{
  "text": "Previous studies have established that Jun plays essential roles in cell growth, survival, migration and invasion, exerting oncogenic roles in various cancers [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Activity of Jun is also critical for the initiation and progression of gastric cancer [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . Chemical compounds and biological factors, such as Helicobacter pylori [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] , often act in gastric cancer through regulating Jun, while its regulation by miRNAs in this disease has not been reported yet. Here we showed that miR-139, a miRNA down-regulated in human gastric cancer, could target Jun for expression inhibition, providing a novel level of regulation for Jun in gastric cancer.",
  "correct_citation": {
